The paper proposes a probabilistic data structure for processing set queries using a small amount of memory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also mentions real-world network traces, indicating that it may belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper addresses the problem of designing a data structure for set queries, which is a common problem in computer networks and security, suggesting that it may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also mentions membership, association, and multiplicity queries, which are common in network analysis and machine learning, suggesting that it may belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) or the Machine Learning (cs.SI) sub-categories.
